title: Safety of Influenza Vaccination Administered During Hospitalization
description: Dr. Sara Tartof, a Researcher at Kaiser Permanente Southern California Department of Research & Evaluation in Pasadena, California, eases concerns in her article appearing online ahead of print in Mayo Clinic Proceedings, which found that the use of influenza vaccinations during hospital stays was safe. She also noted that this practice takes advantage of what otherwise might be a missed opportunity, since after hospitalization, patients are less likely to return for routine flu vaccinations, putting them at risk for contracting influenza. Available at: https://mayocl.in/2SE0U5o
